## 1. Purpose
This policy defines the security controls required on endpoints (laptops, desktops, and mobile devices) that access [COMPANY] systems or data, to prevent endpoints from becoming a path to compromise or PHI exposure — especially important for a distributed/remote workforce.

## 2. Scope
Applies to all endpoints used to access in-scope systems or data, whether [COMPANY]-owned or [approved BYOD — see §6], and to all workforce members and contractors using them. Server/cloud workloads are governed by `configuration-and-hardening-standard.md.template`.

## 3. Policy
1. Endpoints used to access [COMPANY] systems **shall** be enrolled in [COMPANY]'s **MDM/endpoint management** and meet this baseline before and during access.
2. **Full-disk encryption shall be enabled** on all endpoints ([FileVault]/[BitLocker]/[LUKS]) and verified by MDM.
3. **EDR/anti-malware shall be installed, running, and reporting** on all endpoints; tampering with it is prohibited.
4. **Automatic screen lock shall engage after at most [10] minutes** of inactivity and require strong authentication (passcode/biometric); device login **shall** use strong credentials and, where supported, MFA.
5. Endpoints **shall** receive **OS and application security patches** within [the SLAs in `vulnerability-and-patch-management.md.template`]; automatic updates enabled where feasible.
6. **PHI shall not be stored on endpoints except transiently and when strictly necessary;** workforce **shall** access PHI through controlled applications/systems rather than downloading local copies. Where local PHI is unavoidable, it resides only on encrypted, managed devices and is removed when no longer needed (`../asset-data/data-classification-and-handling.md.template`).
7. Host firewall **shall** be enabled; unnecessary services and unauthorized software **shall** be disabled/removed; administrative rights restricted to least privilege.
8. Removable media and external sharing of PHI **shall** be restricted/controlled [per DLP/MDM policy].
9. Lost or stolen devices **shall** be reported immediately and **remotely locked/wiped**; this may trigger `../healthcare/hipaa-breach-notification-procedure.md.template`.
10. On workforce departure or device retirement, endpoints **shall** be wiped/sanitized and access removed (`../access/joiner-mover-leaver-procedure.md.template`).

## 4. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [IT Lead] | Manages MDM, baselines, patch deployment, and device provisioning/retirement. |
| [Security Officer] | Owns this policy; monitors compliance and endpoint security events. |
| Workforce/Contractors | Keep devices compliant; protect credentials; report lost/stolen devices; avoid storing PHI locally. |
| [CTO] | Approves this policy. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 5. Endpoint Baseline (summary)
| Control | Requirement |
|---|---|
| Management | MDM-enrolled and compliant |
| Encryption | Full-disk encryption enabled |
| Malware | EDR running and reporting |
| Lock | Auto-lock ≤ [10] min, strong unlock |
| Patching | Within vulnerability-management SLAs; auto-update on |
| Firewall | Host firewall on |
| Software | Approved software only; least-privilege admin |
| PHI | No persistent local PHI; access via controlled systems |

## 6. BYOD / Contractor Devices
[DECISION: state the org stance.] If BYOD or contractor-owned devices are permitted to access in-scope data, they **shall** meet this baseline (managed profile, encryption, EDR, lock, remote-wipe of [COMPANY] data) and access **shall** be limited; otherwise only [COMPANY]-managed devices may access PHI. Document the chosen approach here.

## 7. Exceptions
Exceptions to this policy require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log.

## 8. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
Compliance is verified through MDM/EDR compliance reporting and periodic audits; non-compliant devices may be blocked from accessing in-scope systems (conditional access). Lost-device and endpoint-compromise events are investigated per `../resilience/incident-response-plan.md.template`. Violations are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

